body:
@sokra Just had a look at the change which sets max size using `Math.max(minSize, maxSize)`

This prevents the crash but the hang during build remains when i use either `enforce: true` or a minSize less then maxSize such as `minSize: 1000,` in the config as follows:

```
optimization: {
    splitChunks: {
      chunks: "initial",
      minSize: 1000,
      //maxSize: 10000,
      cacheGroups: {
        default: false, // disable the built-in groups, default & vendors (vendors is overwritten below)
        vendors: {
          test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]/,
          name: "vendors",
          priority: 10,
          //enforce: true, // create chunk regardless of the size of the chunk
          maxSize: 10000
        }
      }
    }
  },
```

The issue seems to be caused by a loop as the node process starts to use all of the CPU and consumes the RAM at a steady rate.

If maxSize is instead specified at the the splitChunks level as per the following config, it works fine:

```
optimization: {
    splitChunks: {
      chunks: "initial",
      minSize: 1000,
      maxSize: 10000,
      cacheGroups: {
        default: false, // disable the built-in groups, default & vendors (vendors is overwritten below)
        vendors: {
          test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]/,
          name: "vendors",
          priority: 10,
          //enforce: true, // create chunk regardless of the size of the chunk
          //maxSize: 10000
        }
      }
    }
  },
```

The output is as follows:

```
bundle.js  8.62 KiB       0  [emitted]  main~26a0f563
vendors~0928ebd2.11051f8abac033be4592.chunk.js  96.1 KiB       1  [emitted]  vendors~0928ebd2
vendors~53127b40.63e088532ae1ece53785.chunk.js  4.76 KiB       2  [emitted]  vendors~53127b40
vendors~c1dd23ef.781dbcd770ccb43df9c7.chunk.js  7.29 KiB       3  [emitted]  vendors~c1dd23ef
```
The larger chunk is due to the single large 'react-dom' module which is 96KB

There is also another issue when maxSize is used, large single modules larger than maxSize seem to be processed as they are split into 2 chunks, however the second chunk is always almost empty containing no module code.

I don't know for sure but i am guessing that it is not possible to split a single large module into smaller parts?

Either way this is a bug because if the module cant be split it should be left alone and remain as a single chunk, if it can be split then it should be split evenly.

using the following config which splits out 'react-dom'

```
optimization: {
    splitChunks: {
      chunks: "initial",
      minSize: 1000,
      maxSize: 10000,
      cacheGroups: {
        default: false, // disable the built-in groups, default & vendors (vendors is overwritten below)
        reactDom: {
          test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]react-dom[\\/]/,
          name: "vendor.react-dom",
          enforce: true,
          priority: 20
        },
        vendors: {
          test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]/,
          name: "vendors",
          priority: 10,
          //enforce: true, // create chunk regardless of the size of the chunk
          //maxSize: 10000
        }
      }
    }
  },
```

results in the following chunks:

```
bundle.js   8.63 KiB       0  [emitted]  main~26a0f563
vendor.react-dom~0928ebd2.18d3479e1d1e127ecfc1.chunk.js   96.1 KiB       1  [emitted]  vendor.react-dom~0928ebd2
vendor.react-dom~6a83488c.21c9b1ca71c8af4e38ae.chunk.js  312 bytes       2  [emitted]  vendor.react-dom~6a83488c
         vendors~0ba66fd7.70e5f1155bc6aa83b645.chunk.js   1.03 KiB       3  [emitted]  vendors~0ba66fd7
         vendors~53127b40.130f3482b0cc0e62c6ca.chunk.js   4.76 KiB       4  [emitted]  vendors~53127b40
         vendors~55119a63.5f817c5f775bf8ddc54f.chunk.js   6.08 KiB       5  [emitted]  vendors~55119a63
```
Notice the tiny 'react-dom' chunk in the output.

This is how i spotted the original issue as i tried to workaround that behaviour by using maxSize at the cacheGroup level instead of the splitChunks level.

@sokra  I can confirm that https://github.com/webpack/webpack/pull/8416
partially fixes the hang issue.
I tested master after the branch 'bugfix/split-chunks-zero-min' was merged about half an hour ago

It fixes the following config whre maxSize is specified at the cacheGroup level:

```
optimization: {
    splitChunks: {
      chunks: "initial",
      minSize: 1000,
      //maxSize: 10000,
      cacheGroups: {
        default: false, // disable the built-in groups, default & vendors (vendors is overwritten below)
        vendors: {
          test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]/,
          name: "vendors",
          priority: 10,
          //enforce: true, // create chunk regardless of the size of the chunk
          maxSize: 10000
        }
      }
    }
  },
```

but unfortunately does not fix the hang when 'enforce: true' is used in the cacheGroup


```
optimization: {
    splitChunks: {
      chunks: "initial",
      minSize: 1000,
      //maxSize: 10000,
      cacheGroups: {
        default: false, // disable the built-in groups, default & vendors (vendors is overwritten below)
        vendors: {
          test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]/,
          name: "vendors",
          priority: 10,
          enforce: true, // create chunk regardless of the size of the chunk
          maxSize: 10000
        }
      }
    }
  },
```
